---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<section class="px-6 py-16 bg-mantle">
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-8">
    <div class="max-w-2xl flex flex-col gap-6 text-subtext1">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-display text-blue">Why make another editor?</h2>
      <p>
        Rather than being just another text editor, Sev aims to provide a foundation for building text-centric applications.
      </p>
      <p>
        Its user-facing commands and settings are exposed via an embedded Scheme interpreter, making it highly configurable and extensible by end users.
      </p>
      <p>
        It can also build to a desktop executable or to WebAssembly, allowing it to be served directly in the browser.
      </p>
    </div>
    <img
      src={`${base}screenshot.webp`}
      alt="Sev editor showing Scheme configuration code"
      class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-lg"
    />
  </div>
</section>
